g.text: You: "I thought it was an Ace's High moment, Kim."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know about that..." The lieutenant smiles an uncomfortable smile.
Barred Door: It's barred from the inside. You hear the bar rattle in the brackets.
Perception (Hearing): Sounds like it's heavy too. Very sturdy.
Barred Door: This is the door to the pinball workshop that you left barred on the inside.
Pain Threshold: This kind of stuff would hurt -- if not for you not caring about little things like that.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Suck on that, door."

Kim Kitsuragi: "To the workshop behind the wall." He points somewhere within. "This must be the barred door we saw -- we *could* return and open it from the inside." He looks at the door with suspicion.
Physical Instrument: You kick it -- gung ho style, *entering the premises* style -- but the door fails to respect the force. All you hear is the bar rattling inside, laughing at you.
You give it another, more *ferocious* kick. The door still does not move.
Barred Door: The sturdy wood door has lost *all* respect for you.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "I think the brackets broke inside. I've always wanted to know what's in there..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It is not the first closed door we've found in this building -- there is also your mysterious blue kitchen door."

Kim Kitsuragi: "The vigilantes, the cadaver, and..." He nods toward the young woman. "A number of people connected to the case are *in* or around this building. This door is part of it. It's not *unimportant*."
Physical Instrument: It is an unbelievably satisfying sound.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. The further we get, the more this building seems to be tied to the case..."
Physical Instrument: It is an unbelievably satisfying sound.
Electrochemistry: Filling you with a *belief* in your own body.
Shivers: Below, the hostel-cafeteria creaks and groans under your added weight -- a skeleton of composite support beams and cantilevers.
You: Tap on the roof with your foot.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't see how this is going to give new results." He measures the door, stoically. "There must be another way in there."
Inland Empire: No one knows. It is a fleeting feeling.
Perception (Sight): It could be that your eyesight is still too poor to notice it... behind that window.
Perception (Sight): It could be that your eyesight is still too poor to notice it... behind that window.
Inland Empire: Below... in the Union box... was there something behind the window? In the hawthorn branches, brushing against the glass.
You: "See? The main investigation and the door below are merging into a *stereo*-investigation."
You: "I could say something, but I'm not going to, because I don't gloat."
You: "So maybe the door below *is* a *mega*-investigation."
Barred Door: The door receives a thorough disciplining.
Electrochemistry: Its pain and grovelling is much to your liking.
Barred Door: This is a small, heavy door. There is no lock in sight.
The same small, heavy door. No lock in sight.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't see how this is going to give new results." He measures the door, stoically. "There must be another way in there."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Through the kitchen door, perhaps? Let's explore, rather than destroy."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The further we get, the more this building seems to be tied to the case..."
You: "I thought it was an Ace's Low moment, Kim."
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "All right," the woman nods approvingly: "Let's trash the place."

Kim Kitsuragi: "No -- still a mini-investigation." He pretends to make a note in his notebook.
Logic: Must be something valuable inside to go through the trouble of protecting it -- the door is very sturdy indeed.

Kim Kitsuragi: "The vigilantes, the cadaver, and..." He nods to where they young woman once stood. "A number of people connected to the case are *in* or around this building. This door is part of it. It's not *unimportant*."
Half Light: Your foot is ready to explode and punish this *object*!
Barred Door: The door receives a thorough disciplining -- and it doesn't even hurt!
Barred Door: The door receives a thorough disciplining -- at the cost of your foot. Your foot hurts. A lot.
Shivers: A dull thump. Somewhere inside a wind brace rattles from the imperceptible motion of the building.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): The woman takes a drag of her ziggie and nods: "Demolish the place."
Inland Empire: You are a numb, imprecise instrument to ignore this feeling...
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's the barred door we saw." He looks at the door with suspicion. "I don't know why we didn't open it from the inside -- we *should*."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I hate it when that happens."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should search downstairs, in the kitchen -- just in case. Maybe there's a door that leads up, that we don't know of."
Physical Instrument: Something cracks inside. It is an unbelievably satisfying sound.
This time -- something cracks inside. It is an unbelievably satisfying sound.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know." He makes a note in his notebook.
"I don't know, lieutenant-yefreitor." He makes a note.
Klaasje (Miss Oranje Disco Dancer): "Nice." The young woman nods.
Logic: The key... to the kitchen door. From behind the window. Use it on the door.
Physical Instrument: Something cracks inside. It is an unbelievably satisfying sound.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Sounds like the property damage wasn't in vain, at least. Would it hurt to look in?"
"Well," the lieutenant cups his ear. "Sounds like *this time* the property damage was at least resultive. Would it hurt to look in?"
Kim Kitsuragi: He doesn't say anything.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We should search downstairs. There are things about this building we don't know yet."
Physical Instrument: The door is oblivious to your distress.
